ionate, fair, and unbiased account of Armstrong's thought which considers the areas of weakness in his work while encouraging further debate.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPhilosophyzAustralia. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077359494440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773594944423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773594944/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles